Description:
Pair statue depicting husband and wife, seated upon a high backed chair, with arms around extended around each others shoulders. The man wears a long white kilt, and is depicted with red skin, while the woman wears a tight-fitting ankle-length white dress; her skin is depicted as light yellow. Both wear elaborate layered wigs.
The statue is uninscribed.
The sides of the chair are decorated with a scalloped motif, edged on two sides with a decorative border of rectangles.;

